    "Body": "Polymath  Polymath 4.5 ????????????\u0098\u0085 Business Development Specialist (APAC) Toronto Apply Now Save Job Company Rating Salary Reviews Location Polymath is an interface between financial securities and the blockchain, helping issuers to overcome the complex technical and legal challenges related to issuing regulated securities on the blockchain. We are a group of start-up veterans, legal experts, finance professionals, and all-star developers looking to hire a highly strategic and tactical Business Development Specialist (APAC region) to join our dynamic team. As our Business Development Specialist, you\u2019ll leverage effective sales tactics to strike business and community partnerships with various participants in the securities and blockchain ecosystems. You\u2019ll need to understand the challenges and complexities of the financial sector and blossom into that Subject Matter Expert on Security Tokens and Blockchain. You have consistently achieved or over-achieved your targets and have experience closing and growing large partnerships in the financial industry, or adjacent markets. You will manage the entire sales process, developing leads into successful partners. You have a strong desire to learn about security tokens and their impact on financial markets and blockchain in general. Locational Preference: Tokyo, Japan; Singapore; Seoul, South Korea; Hong Kong, China Responsibilities: Strategically navigate through sales cycle with precision and focus on presenting the value of Polymath\u2019s solutions to all levels of prospective partners, including C-level executives. Identify, engage and close partnerships with regulated entities to run nodes on Polymesh and act as validators on our blockchain. Interact and meet with local and international regulators to drive adoption of ERC-1400 token standard. Negotiate and close partnerships; act as ambassador to the product team and help with onboarding new business partners. Work closely with team to refine your craft and optimize your market penetration strategy for optimal management of your defined target market. Keep up-to-date on market intel to develop rapport with customers through communication. Grow local awareness of Polymath through meetups, conferences, hackathons, social media (WeChat, Telegram) and other community engagements. Translating English communication materials (whitepapers, Medium articles) into local language(s). Qualifications: Business degree or related field of study 5+ years sales and/or business development experience; minimum of 2 years in APAC markets. Ability to prospect partners across entire APAC region, travelling when needed. Practical experience in Capital Markets (securities lending, KYC/KYB, onboarding, listing, clearing, settlement) including compliance. Experience in signing large transactions/closing large partnerships. Experience crafting sales strategies for your vertical and executing on your account plans. Experience prospecting and validating inbound as well as outbound leads. Strong communication and presentation skills (phone, video, email, in-person). Ability to work with team members across multiple time zones. Fluency in the native language(s) of your local region. Mix of virtual and client facing presentations. Competitive by nature and strong desire to continue to learn. Value driven approach Nice to have: Understanding of blockchain, cryptocurrencies, security tokens etc. Previous start-up experience Remote working experience Get alerts to jobs like this, to your inbox. ", 
